article.description: Yates, Cleveland State hold off Oakland, 65-61
article.headline: Yates, Cleveland State hold off Oakland, 65-61
article.linkText: Yates, Cleveland State hold off Oakland, 65-61
article.story: CLEVELAND -- Andre Yates scored all 14 of his points in the second half and Cleveland State held off Oakland for a 65-61 win on Thursday night. Yates picked up two quick fouls and played only about 4 minutes in the first half, but Cleveland State (9-8, 3-0 Horizon League) opened up a 19-2 lead as Oakland started the game shooting 1-of-10 from the field. Vinny Zollo's 3 with 10:18 left in the half made it 24-6 before the Vikings missed their next 10 field goals and Oakland (5-11, 1-1) used a 22-3 run to take its first lead, 28-27, with 3 minutes left. Cleveland State took a 34-30 lead into halftime. Yates, who played 18 minutes in the second half, scored eight -- including back-to-back 3's -- during a 12-4 run that pushed Cleveland State's lead to 53-42 with 13 minutes left. Jalen Hays' layup with 2:15 to go pulled Oakland within 63-61, but the Golden Grizzlies missed their final five shots.
